#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:103
msgid "Why on earth are we paying twice for the same electrons?"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:105
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On bright days the peninsula often makes more solar than the local "
"grid can swallow. Instead of\n"
"    using every electron we grew for free, we leave it on the table while"
" other kit keeps running—\n"
"    and households foot the bill for flexibility twice. Politely put: "
"that should embarrass us.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:112
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What would actually help?</strong> Grids and storage we stop "
"talking about and start building,\n"
"    plus price signals that pay people to use clean power when the sun is"
" generous. Less waste, lower\n"
"    bills, fewer excuses. We know what to do.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:121
msgid "City-sized anger"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:123
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today’s pile of unused solar is in the same league as the daily use "
"of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> ordinary homes (illustrative %(kwh)s kWh "
"per home per day—not a census,\n"
"    see methodology). That’s not abstract; that’s kitchens and lights "
"someone could have run for free.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:132
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:134
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The waste you see is real enough to measure—which is the infuriating "
"part. Quarter-hourly unused\n"
"    solar (MWh) comes from Red Eléctrica de España (REE) data, then "
"through a separate pipeline into\n"
"    this project’s database: rows keyed by date_day with qh_1_mwh through"
" qh_100_mwh (15-minute buckets).\n"
"    Same calendar day, multiple rows: we sum buckets before showing "
"anything.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:142
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars "
"(Europe/Madrid calendar day). Any slots\n"
"    beyond the first 96 are folded into the last hour of the day. Day "
"totals are the sum of all\n"
"    quarter-hour values. “So far this year” uses SUM(total_mwh) across "
"rows from 1 January through the\n"
"    selected date. The average “per hour” figure is the mean of the 24 "
"hourly bars (equivalently the\n"
"    day total divided by 24).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:151
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro figures only appear if WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH is set: a blunt "
"illustrative rate × energy,\n"
"    not a market invoice—still useful for remembering this isn’t “free” "
"in anyone’s pocket.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:156
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr ""

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:158
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable illustrative kWh/day "
"figure to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale; replace or calibrate it when you publish official assumptions."
"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

